 butter, water and ½ teaspoon of the salt into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer onto a silicone bread  mat or a lightly floured work surface and shape into a tight ball. Wrap in plastic wrap and place into refrigerator to rest for a minimum of 15 minutes. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. On a silicone bread mat or a lightly floured work surface, roll out pastry to 5 mm thickness. Line a round, loose-bottom tart tin (25 cm) with pastry. Cover and place into refrigerator to firm for 5 minutes."},{"content":"Line pastry case with baking paper, then fill with pie weights, rice or dried beans. Bake for 10-15 minutes (180°C) or until pastry is dry to the touch, but not coloured. Remove pie weights and bake for a further 3-5 minutes (180°C), until pastry is just cooked. Remove pastry case, place onto a baking tray and set aside. Reduce oven to 160°C."},{"content":"Place ginger, coriander and oil into mixing bowl and blend <b>5 sec\/speed 10<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Blend <b>5 sec\/speed 10<b> or to a coarse paste. Spread mixture over base of pastry case, then scatter crab meat over ginger paste. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place sour cream, eggs, egg yolks, salt and pepper into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Pour over crab meat, then bake for 30-35 minutes (160°C) or until just set. Garnish with rocket, then serve while warm with Chilli dressing on the side."}],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 30m","8 portions"]}